Key takeways from the above data¶

- Fashion-MNIST is based on Zalando's article images.¶

- Training Set: 60,000 examples¶

- Test Set: 10,000 examples¶

- Each example is a 28x28 grayscale image from color values ranging from 0 to 255¶

- Labeling: Associated with a label from one of 10 classes.¶

In [ ]:
train_images, x_val, train_labels, y_val = train_test_split(train_images, train_labels, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

train_images = train_images.reshape((-1, 28 * 28)) / 255.0
x_val = x_val.reshape((-1, 28 * 28)) / 255.0
test_images = test_images.reshape((-1, 28 * 28)) / 255.0

train_labels = to_categorical(train_labels, 10)
y_val = to_categorical(y_val, 10)
test_labels = to_categorical(test_labels, 10)
In [ ]:
def deepNN(neurons, hidden, activation, optimizer, epochs=10, batch_size=32):
    model = models.Sequential()
    
    model.add(layers.Dense(neurons, activation=activation, input_shape=(28 * 28,)))
    
    for _ in range(hidden):
        model.add(layers.Dense(neurons, activation=activation))
    
    model.add(layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax'))

    model.compile(optimizer=optimizer,
                  loss='categorical_crossentropy',
                  metrics=['accuracy'])

    history = model.fit(train_images, train_labels,
                        epochs=epochs,
                        batch_size=batch_size,
                        validation_data=(x_val, y_val),
                        verbose=2)

    return model, history

In [ ]:
def evaluate_model(model, test_images, test_labels):
    y_pred = model.predict(test_images)
    y_pred_classes = np.argmax(y_pred, axis=1)
    y_true = np.argmax(test_labels, axis=1)

    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred_classes)
    confusion_mat = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred_classes)

    print(f"Accuracy: {accuracy * 100:.2f}%")
    
    print("\n Classification report :")
    print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred_classes))
    
    print("\nConfusion Matrix:")
    print(confusion_mat)

    incorrect_indices = np.where(y_pred_classes != y_true)[0]

    fig, ax = plot.subplots(figsize=(12,8))
    sb.heatmap(
        confusion_mat, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Greens', xticklabels=labels.values(), yticklabels=labels.values()
    )
    plot.title('Confusion Matrix for the model ')
    plot.xlabel('Predicted Label')
    plot.ylabel('True Label')
    plot.show()

    print("\n")

    plot.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    for i in range(10):
        plot.subplot(2, 5, i + 1)
        idx = incorrect_indices[i]
        plot.imshow(test_images[idx].reshape((28, 28)), cmap='gray')
        plot.title(f"True: {y_true[idx]}\nPred: {y_pred_classes[idx]}")
        plot.axis('off')
    plot.title("Incorrect classifications")
    plot.show()

    return accuracy, confusion_mat
